A roadside bomb targeted a vehicle belonging to the Islamic Emirate forces on Sunday in Faizabad, the capital of Afghanistan's northeast Badakhshan province, leaving one child injured, TOLO News reported. Three people were also injured after another blast outside a moneychanger market in the city of Kunduz, the capital of Afghanistan's northern Kunduz province, on Sunday morning. They were taken to hospital, according to the provincial head of health department Najibullah Sahel. Blasts were also reported in Kunar province on the same day. (With input from Xinhua News Agency)